verbose_text: Subsequently, nuclear factor-kappaB (NF-kappaB) and transcription factor activated activator protein-1 are activated, while the release of pro inflammatory cytokines, including IL-6, IL-1 and TNF-alpha is promoted, inducing the downstream cascade of inflammatory reactions, resulting in tissue inflammatory injury.
